      {
        "id": "nuxt-foundations",
        "title": "1. Nuxt Foundations",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "1. Built on Vue 3",
            "subtitle": "The power of the Composition API and Vite."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Vue 3 & Composition API",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🧩",
                  "text": "<strong>Modular:</strong> Composition API for better logic reuse."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "⚡",
                  "text": "<strong>Fast:</strong> Built-in support for Vite for instant dev starts."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Nuxt 3 is built from the ground up for Vue 3, leveraging its high performance and modularity."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Auto-Imports",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🪄",
                  "text": "<strong>Seamless:</strong> No need to manually import `ref`, `computed`, or components."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "📦",
                  "text": "<strong>Tree-shaken:</strong> Only the code you use is included in the build."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Zero-config development with automatic imports for components, composables, and Vue APIs."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "File-based Routing",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "📂",
                  "text": "<strong>pages/:</strong> Automatically generates routes based on folder structure."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🏗️",
                  "text": "<strong>layouts/:</strong> Reusable UI shells for your pages."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Define your application structure through the filesystem."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Universal Rendering",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🌍",
                  "text": "<strong>SSR:</strong> Fast initial load and excellent SEO."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🏎️",
                  "text": "<strong>Hydration:</strong> Seamless transition to a single-page app in the browser."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Nuxt handles both server-side and client-side rendering out of the box."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "nitro-engine",
        "title": "2. The Nitro Engine",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "2. High-Performance Runtime",
            "subtitle": "The engine that powers Nuxt 3."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "What is Nitro?",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🚀",
                  "text": "<strong>Fast:</strong> Built with Rollup and Unjs packages."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "📦",
                  "text": "<strong>Portable:</strong> Deploy to any runtime without modification."
                }
              ],
              "title": "A portable, performant, and lightweight server engine for Node.js and the Edge."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Built-in Storage (Unstorage)",
            "box": {
              "code": "// server/api/data.js\nconst storage = useStorage('data');\nawait storage.setItem('key', { value: 'nitro' });",
              "title": "A unified storage layer for different drivers (Redis, FS, Cloudflare KV)."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Server API Routes",
            "box": {
              "code": "export default defineEventHandler((event) => {\n  return { hello: 'world' };\n});",
              "title": "Create type-safe API routes easily in the `server/api` directory."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Server Middleware",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🛡️",
                  "text": "<strong>Security:</strong> Add headers or validation."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🔍",
                  "text": "<strong>Logging:</strong> Track request performance."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Intercept and handle requests on the server side before they reach your components."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "nuxt-data-fetching",
        "title": "3. Data Fetching Mastery",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "3. Universal Data Handling",
            "subtitle": "Mastering useFetch and useAsyncData."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "useFetch",
            "box": {
              "code": "const { data, pending, error } = await useFetch('/api/users');",
              "title": "The most common way to fetch data in Nuxt. Isomorphic and SSR-friendly."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "useAsyncData",
            "box": {
              "code": "const { data } = await useAsyncData('users', () => $fetch('/api/users'));",
              "title": "Flexible data fetching for complex scenarios or when using non-fetch sources (e.g., SDKs)."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Isomorphic $fetch",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🏎️",
                  "text": "<strong>Direct Call:</strong> Skips the network layer when on the server."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🧩",
                  "text": "<strong>Consistent:</strong> Same API everywhere."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Nuxt provides `$fetch` which works on both server and client, calling server routes directly on the server to save overhead."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Refresh and Watch",
            "box": {
              "code": "useFetch('/api/search', { watch: [query] });",
              "title": "Automatically re-fetch data when reactive parameters change."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "nuxt-rendering-modes",
        "title": "4. Rendering Modes",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "4. Hybrid & Edge Rendering",
            "subtitle": "Tailoring rendering to your needs."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Static vs Dynamic",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "📄",
                  "text": "<strong>SSG:</strong> Static Site Generation for speed and cost."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🌊",
                  "text": "<strong>SSR:</strong> Server-Side Rendering for real-time data."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Choosing the right strategy for each route in your application."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)",
            "box": {
              "code": "// nuxt.config.ts\nrouteRules: {\n  '/blog/**': { isr: 3600 }\n}",
              "title": "Update static content in the background after deployment without a full rebuild."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Stale-While-Revalidate (SWR)",
            "box": {
              "code": "routeRules: {\n  '/api/data': { swr: true }\n}",
              "title": "Serve cached content immediately and refresh it in the background."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Nuxt Islands & Server Components",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🏝️",
                  "text": "<strong>Islands:</strong> Render a component on the server with zero client JS."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🚀",
                  "text": "<strong>Efficient:</strong> Reduce the payload size significantly."
                }
              ],
              "title": "The experimental future of server-only components in Nuxt."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
